bibdata.title: Step through browse list generation and document for go-live

comments.body:
Current strategy:

This takes two commands. My strategy to get a total time is to do the following:

1. `time bundle exec rake browse:all`
```
real    323m45.142s
user    197m41.286s
sys     1m13.911s
```
2. `time bundle exec rake browse:load_all`
  * Note: In QA I had to run `OL_DB_PORT=5432 time bundle exec rake browse:load_all`, the port being defined is important.
  ```
103.02user 34.66system 26:29.50elapsed 8%CPU (0avgtext+0avgdata 112652maxresident)k
0inputs+10337680outputs (0major+84844minor)pagefaults 0swaps
  ```
  I'm not sure what happened here, I think this says it took 26 minutes.

Current estimate: ~ 6 hours.

then add them together. If they both go fine, and there's still time, I'll try `time /bin/bash -c "OL_DB_PORT=5432 bundle exec rake browse:all && OL_DB_PORT=5432 bundle exec rake browse:load_all"`

comments.body:
The news story has been updated, so we can link to that (replacing the Hathi block):

>[System Upgrades This Summer](https://library.princeton.edu/news/general/2021-08-02/pul-launch-new-library-system-summer-2021-hathitrust-etas-update)
A system upgrade this summer will replace a 20-year-old platform and provide more efficient and easier access to library resources. This is a behind-the-scenes process and will not result in any changes in the catalog itself. Requesting materials through the catalog will not be available from July 22 through July 27, and requesting items from ReCAP will not be available from July 16 to August 8. Please see [our announcement](https://library.princeton.edu/news/general/2021-08-02/pul-launch-new-library-system-summer-2021-hathitrust-etas-update) for more information.
There will be some changes to catalog, especially the account /  login stuff. Should we soften "will not result in any changes in the catalog itself"?
